<TEXT>
vicki mercers job as a waitress at 
stellas goodie house was easier before this workingclass town of 
4000 became part of a study aimed at reducing heart disease in 
rural america 
they want dry toast now or a dry bagel or muffin she said 
and they want diet dressings on their salads but what really 
gets me is theyll order deepfried fish or chicken and pick off 
the breading or ill have to blot all the grease off with a 
napkin 
the fuss is apparently paying off for her customers who compare 
cholesterol readings blood pressures and body fat measurements in 
casual conversation 
when we started this everyone called us fat city program 
director bill reger said tuesday now were being recognized as 
one of the most fit towns in the country 
the results of the 33 million lifestyle modification study 
have been encouraging reger said 
twice as many participants exercise regularly compared to when 
the study began in may 1988 and nearly all 1000 participants have 
reduced their intake of fat salt and cholesterol reger said 
participants blood pressures cholesterol levels weight and 
other cardiovascular risk factors were checked every three months 
tests earlier this year found more than half the participants 
had lowered their average cholesterol readings by 15 points from 
2213 to 2063 a reading below 200 is desirable according to the 
american heart association 
their average weight dropped from 1694 pounds to 1664 pounds 
they also reduced their blood pressure by an average of 5 points 
and lowered their resting pulse rates by four beats per minute 
results of the studys final health screening in april will be 
released june 9 
reger said the most substantial improvement has been in the 
cholesterol readings 
theres no more red meat as far as im concerned said mary 
jo kull 68 whose cholesterol plunged from 266 to 177 i eat 
fruits vegetables pastas brown rice i even bake my own bread so 
i can control the amount of fat and fiber 
i put jelly or applesauce on bread instead of margarine 
the programs impact is evident at stellas and other wellsburg 
restaurants where steamed vegetables fruit plates and oat bran 
bagels have replaced mashed potatoes and gravy ice cream and 
doughnuts as favorites 
the study aimed at developing a health education program for 
rural areas was sponsored by the bayer co and glenbrook 
laboratories the aspirinmakers new yorkbased parent 
organizers said they chose wellsburg situated on the ohio 
river 45 miles southwest of pittsburgh because of its small 
population west virginia registered the nations highest obesity 
rate at 24 percent in a 1986 federal study 
</TEXT>
