screen after more than 10 years away in daddy nostalgie a 
french production shown at the 43rd cannes film festival 
directed by bernard tavernier the film screened monday depicts 
a dying man bogarde trying to rebuild emotional ties with his 
family particularly his daughter played by english actress jane 
birkin 
bogarde 69 portrays a man suffering both physically and 
spiritually knowing he is doomed and has lost touch with his 
family 
filmed on the cote dazur in sunny settings near and in cannes 
the poignant story concerns a bilingual family with the dying 
mans french wife played by french musical comedy and stage 
actress odette laure 
bogarde gives a strong performance as the father who wants to 
drink philosophize and live it up as much as possible before he 
dies 
bogarde who has been in semiretirement for 11 years writing 
novels and autobiographic works in the south of france said at a 
news conference that when bernard taverniers offer came through 
i took it 
the actor known for films such as night porter and 
providence said he had received few tempting script offers 
during his semiretirement and added that maybe this will be my 
last 
travernier said the bilingual aspect was key to the fim 
i used englishborn actors like bogarde and birkin because i 
wanted language to be a dramatic force in the film he said 
bogarde said for me the most tragic moment was when i said 
to miche his wife you never speak english to me any more 
tavernier who was praised at cannes for his 1984 dimanche a 
la campagne sunday in the country said bogarde and birkin added 
to the english dialogue as the movie progressed 
lets ad lib tavernier recalls telling his actors when i 
saw the crew with tears in their eyes i knew something was 
happening im proud of the film 
