east germany was one of the soviet unions staunchest allies 
under the german states former hardline communist leaders 
eppelmann said it will be necessary to hold the warsaw pact 
together as a political alliance at least for an interim period 
he said he was pressing for a total european solution to 
defense issues 
moscow officials already have proposed the breakup of the 
opposing military alliances the north atlantic treaty organization 
and the warsaw pact but those proposals have been met with 
skepticism in washington 
europeans in recent months have been talking increasingly about 
a continental solution for security issues as the various nations 
come closer together 
the question of military alliances and allegiances is a major 
point in the continuing german unification talks 
moscow says a united germany cannot remain in nato the united 
states west germany and their allies insist on such a membership 
west germanys foreign minister hansdietrich genscher has 
offered to let soviet troops stay in what is now east germany for a 
