china stands to lose nearly onefourth of its 
total exports and most of its sales to the united states if 
washington cancels its mostfavorednation trade status the vice 
minister of trade said today 
we are very concerned that the good economic and trade 
relations the two countries have established over the past 10 years 
could be destroyed the minister shen jueren said in an 
interview with american journalists 
he estimated china would lose about 10 billion worth of exports 
annually an even greater loss than us analysts have estimated 
china exported about 43 billion worth of goods worldwide last 
year including about 12 billion worth to the united states 
