chinese exports to the united states would fall 50 percent 
shen said some chinese workers would lose their jobs especially 
in exportoriented coastal provinces but did not provide any 
figures 
china is a large country and we can bear the burden if we have 
to shen said 
china and the united states have given each other 
mostfavorednation trade status since 1980 entitling each to the 
lowest available tariffs on exported goods without it the average 
tariff on chinese goods would jump to more than 50 percent from the 
current 9 percent the uschina business council estimates 
chinas status must be renewed each year with june 3 the 
deadline for a decision president bush is expected to support 
renewing the special trade status but may face stiff opposition 
from congressmen who believe china should be punished for last 
junes crackdown on the studentled prodemocracy movement 
