<TEXT>
china has canceled a 550 million deal with a 
us defense contractor to modernize its f8 fighter jets the 
state department said today 
under the 1986 deal grumman corp was to equip the planes with 
sophisticated electronics and navigation and radar equipment 
the chinese government has decided not to proceed beyond the 
development phase at this time said richard boucher the state 
dpartments deputy spokesman 
boucher declined to speculate on the reasons for the decision or 
the employment impact at grumman he said the development phase of 
the project will be completed this fall 
but a us official who commented on condition he not be 
identified said the chinese apparently were concerned about rising 
costs and the fact that immediate delivery of the sophisticated 
gear is barred by the ban on military exports imposed by the united 
states after the crushing of chinas prodemocracy movement 
we have not made any deliveries and we will not make any until 
circumstances change boucher said 
they made the decision they didnt want to proceed with the 
production phase lt cmdr edward lundquist a pentagon 
spokesman told the los angeles times earlier 
the chinese embassy in washington would not comment on the 
decision however the times quoted unidentified defense industry 
sources as saying the chinese had expressed concern over cost 
overruns on the project 
dubbed peace pearl the agreement ranked among the largest of 
its kind reached between china and the united states in the 1980s 
the deal was touted at the time as the basis for strategic 
cooperation against the soviet union 
under peace pearl the chinese air force and grumman based in 
bethpage ny were to upgrade 55 planes at 10 million each but 
one unidentified industry analyst told the times the cost overruns 
could total 200 million 
mariam reid a grumman spokeswoman referred questions about the 
deal to the pentagon 
the bush administration suspended us military sales and 
deliveries to china last year after the government crushed the 
prodemocracy movement 
the administration also expelled 40 chinese officers assigned to 
the peace pearl project at grumman in bethpage and at 
wrightpatterson air force base near dayton ohio but it allowed 
longterm military programs such as peace pearl to continue and 
eventually allowed the chinese officers to return to the united 
states 
the arms modernization pact was signed in 1986 after 
thendefense secretary caspar w weinberger offered the idea during 
a 1983 trip to beijing 
