acquistion said he does not expect the naval review scheduled to 
be completed this summer to produce the same results as the 
aircraft review 
im personally confident that when were through with this 
that both the ssn21 and the ddg51 will be validated as proper 
ships to be built cann told the panel 
the assistant secretary also assured the panel that he is 
confident the seawolf will work although half of the funds for the 
nearly 35 billion program will be appropriated before operational 
tests have been completed 
i have relatively high expectations that once we put the 
seawolf together it will do very well cann said 
vice adm dl cooper the assistant chief of naval operations 
for undersea warfare said a study by the cia and defense 
intelligence agency concluded that the submarine in the fleet in 
1995 will be superior to the best threat it might face in the year 
2005 
