rounded up people in six villages and shot many before fleeing the 
rebels april 9 
at that time the soldiers were about 30 miles north of the 
strategic port of buchanan about 60 miles southeast of monrovia 
the capital 
the 15 bodies displayed monday deep inside rebel territory were 
in a freshly dug grave that had not been filled in because 
villagers fled to avoid the fighting the survivors said they were 
interviewed in a hospital on the liberian agriculture corp rubber 
plantation an americanowned operation 
