west germany on tuesday called for 
united german elections as early as december and the proposal drew 
angry responses from opposition politicians in both german nations 
markus meckel east germanys foreign minister and head of the 
east german social democrats said he feared early joint elections 
could result in east germans being dominated in an allgerman 
state 
the east berlin government announced that it plans to hold state 
elections dec 2 the same day as the west german national 
elections 
it was not clear whether the announcement from eberhard stief 
the no 2 official in the east german interior ministry was 
designed as an intermediary step on the way to plans for joint 
national elections in both countries 
west german chancellor helmut kohl met with his own coalition 
partners tuesday to look over a draft treaty that will seal the 
economic merger of the two germanys on july 2 
kohls coalition partners gave their approval to the treaty 
during the session but a few details remain to be worked out 
the planned economic merger wasnt the only topic at the 
closeddoor meeting 
hans klein kohls chief spokesman said all participants 
spoke out unanimously for the soonest possible date for 
allgerman elections 
he did not give a possible date 
but alfred dregger parliamentary leader of kohls christian 
democrats said he favors either replacing the dec 2 federal 
elections with allgerman balloting or holding the allgerman vote 
when the current legislative period ends jan 13 1991 
finance minister theo waigel said he believed an allgerman vote 
would be held this year 
after the meeting kohl said he had not discarded the idea of 
holding federal elections dec 2 but he again left open the 
possibility the german states could hold a joint federal election 
that day 
kohl said that question must be decided in the parliament of 
east germany 
the chancellor said allgerman elections could not occur until 
conclusion of the socalled twoplusfour unification talks 
involving the two german nations and four world war ii victors 
the soviet union the united states britain and france 
the six nations are trying to iron out the international 
complexities of unification such as the military attachments of a 
united germany kohl said he is confident those talks can be 
concluded this year 
kohl suffered a major setback earlier in the week after losing 
control of parliaments upper house to the opposition social 
democrats through two state election defeats 
earlier this month the chancellor had said he did not see 
allgerman elections occurring before the fall of 1991 
but now kohl possibly sensing he would have a better chance of 
winning allgerman elections than the federal vote dec 2 has left 
open the possibility of the joint elections before next year 
