coalition allies tuesday determined the economic merger will take 
effect on july 2 as planned 
klein said a few important details remain to be worked out 
but that kohl was confident that would occur during a meeting 
between the german finance ministers in bonn on thursday 
he said one of the problems was the lack of information about 
east germanys current economic situation the economic merger 
would involve a drastic overhaul of east germanys embattled 
economy in exchange for massive west german assistance 
under the draft economic treaty east germany would turn over 
all currency matters to west germanys central bank and bring its 
economic policies in line with those of its western neighbor 
