gates is a reflection of bushs deep concern about the 
deteriorating situation in the region which has been at the center 
of two indianpakistani wars 
gates may 1921 trip is designed to convey bushs message 
firsthand to the leaders of both countries and gain a firsthand 
appreciation of the situation fitzwater said 
accompanying gates will be assistant secretary of state john 
kelly and richard haas the national security councils top expert 
on the region 
