supporters said passage would set the stage for more sweeping 
electoral reform to would limit political horsetrading 
four separate bills on direct election of the premier were 
submitted for the first of three readings needed for the measure 
to become law 
under the current system voters chose from a selection of 
national party lists the head of the party with the most seats has 
by tradition become prime minister if he can form a coalition 
government 
under all proposals submitted tuesday the prime minister would 
be elected separately from the rest of the candidates for 
parliament a premier would no longer be as dependent on the 
support of small parties to stay in office 
the proposals varied as to the length of the premiers term of 
office and the number of votes in parliament needed to remove him 
