worked on the law as saying the measure would add 77 billion to 
the states current annual pension outlay of 108 billion 
the law comes at a time when the soviet government is struggling 
with a large budget deficit but also promising aid to lowincome 
groups to ease the coming transition to a marketbased economy 
under president mikhail s gorbachev prices are expected to rise 
and unemployment to grow 
to ease the burden on the state budget the law will be 
introduced in stages coming into full force in three years tass 
said 
