twenty years ago tuesday jackson state 
students and staff swept up broken glass counted bullet holes and 
tried to understand why police killed two people and wounded a 
dozen during a vietnam war protest 
since students and staff were between semesters the anniversary 
of the killings passed quietly on the campus where a dormitory wall 
remains pockmarked by gunfire 
