dubbed peace pearl the agreement ranked among the largest 
military arrangements between china and the united states in the 
1980s and was hailed as a basis for strategic cooperation against 
the soviet union 
the arrangement called for the chinese air force and grumman 
based in bethpage ny to upgrade 55 planes at 10 million each 
one unidentified industry analyst told the los angeles times 
that cost overruns could boost the price tag to 750 million 
the administration not only barred military sales and deliveries 
but also expelled 40 chinese military officers assigned to the 
peace pearl project at grumman in bethpage and at wrightpatterson 
air force base near dayton ohio 
