administration 
technicians working on a makeshift platform in columbias 
payload bay began draining toxic freon refrigerant from the 
shuttles cooling system friday they completed the work late 
monday then cut out the valve about the length of a hand and 
some attached plumbing 
it was the first time a cooling valve had ever been removed at 
the launch pad the 100 million astro observatory columbias 
payload located about 10 feet below the workers platform remained 
safe under protective nets 
