service center for analysis rockwell built columbia and the other 
shuttles 
pieces of the torn metal filter were found on two other filters 
on the valve malone said pipes next to the removed valve were 
being checked for clues as to why the filter may have torn and to 
assure there are no other problems 
after a new valve is installed probably on wednesday the 
cooling system will be refilled with freon and the entire system 
will be tested malone said 
nasa was expected to set a new launch date early next week once 
the work is completed 
