after its first note tuesday 
based on notes from the jury burns speculated that the panel 
was at an impasse over the discrimination and homicide charges 
he predicted the judge would give the jurors a socalled allen 
charge wednesday if they continued to report a deadlock 
under an allen charge a judge formally admonishes deadlocked 
jurors to persist and listen to each other with an open mind 
prosecutors say that if the panel is unable to decide all 
counts the judge would have to accept a verdict on whatever 
charges it did agree on the defendant then would be retried on the 
charges on which the jury was deadlocked 
