prince charles called on society tuesday to make 
greater use of the skills and energies of retired people 
people tend to take retirement seriously they withdraw into 
the anterooms of society and often do little or nothing stagnating 
and wilting visibly they act out the role in which society has 
cast them he said 
the 41yearold heir to the british throne said greater 
initiatives were needed to tap the skills experience enthusiasm 
and time of retired people 
to retired people he said look about your community ask 
yourselves how your talents and those of your friends could be used 
to benefit not only others but yourselves too 
