letter of life it is or could be the final glorious concluding 
paragraph he said 
and the challenge is in part how do we offer these millions 
some opportunity to find the right mix of leisure with constructive 
and worthwhile activity he said 
the prince also noted it was a harsh and terrible fact that 
so many old people were lonely 
it is one of the sad paradoxes of this earthly life that 
alongside the advantages of an industrial society we have witnessed 
the parallel degradation of the wider family circle and an 
expansion of the kind of loneliness which is still less common in 
other parts of europe 
