<TEXT>
people conducting drug deals in their 
public housing units could lose their leases without being charged 
with a crime under a program housing secretary jack kemp unveiled 
tuesday 
a judicial order for forfeiture of assets is a very powerful 
weapon kemp told several hundred state and local drug war 
officials at a conference called by the office of national drug 
control policy it allows the public housing authority to take 
over the traffickers unit immediately 
kemps proposal was announced as officials elsewhere in the bush 
administration were readying a package of other antidrug measures 
to be sent to congress on wednesday 
a provision of that package would give the immigration and 
naturalization service greater authority to deport noncitizens 
without hearings 
duke austin chief spokesman for the service said it would add 
a small number of serious drug offenses such as trafficking or 
possession with intent to distribute to the list of serious crimes 
for which conviction can bring deportation without hearings 
those hearings and subsequent appeals can take two years 
the housing program which kemp said will start next month drew 
immediate criticism from the american civil liberties union 
kemp said it targeted serious drug traffickers because the 
standard of proof for a forfeiture order is evidence beyond a 
reasonable doubt that the apartment has been used for the 
commission of a drug felony 
congress specifically identified leases as forfeitable assets in 
the 1988 antidrug act said bud albright jr deputy general 
counsel for the department of housing and urban development 
the public housing asset forfeiture demonstration project to be 
launched by hud and the justice department and carried out by local 
housing authorities with local us attorneys will be conducted in 
23 cities nationwide kemp declined to identify them 
in addition kemp said hud is proposing new regulations for 
section 8 rent subsidies those he said will ensure that persons 
convicted of drugrelated or violent crimes and evicted from public 
housing will not be allowed to use section 8 vouchers for other 
rental property 
albright said the regulations should be sent to the office of 
management and budget on wednesday and should be published in the 
federal register next month 
the aclu said the proposal takes a solid principle of american 
jurisprudence which is that you are innocent until proven guilty 
and turns it on its head 
it suggests the government can punish people in advance of a 
conviction aclu spokeswoman colleen oconnor said 
it also discriminates against people who are poor and 
dependent on federal programs and turns a program designed to 
help people into a means of enforcing the drug laws she added 
albright said some individual public housing authorities already 
have seized leases from drug traffickers but the program announced 
by kemp will be a nationwide hit to raise the consciousness of 
drug dealers and of the public that this is something we can use 
and we intend to use 
</TEXT>
