<TEXT>
ibm said tuesday it would enhance its callpath 
software which links corporate phone systems with computer data 
bases so that the software will work with many brands of phone 
systems 
currently callpath only works with phone systems made by rolm 
the telephone equipment maker owned jointly by international 
business machines corp and siemens ag of west germany 
callpath allows a company such as a mail order house to link an 
incoming phone call from a customer with that customers records in 
the companys ibm computer the system displays the customers 
records on a computer screen in front of a customer service 
representative as the employee answers the phone 
callpath also allows a company to transfer both a telephone call 
from a customer and that customers computerized records from one 
employee to another such as from a customer service representative 
to a supervisor 
callpath works through corporate phone systems called private 
branch exchanges or pbxs 
ibm said two additional telephone equipment makers siemens and 
northern telecom inc have announced their pbxs will have the 
capability to be linked to the enhanced callpath 
ibm also said it has reached an agreement with american 
telephone amp telegraph co to work on making callpath compatibrgicenter 
said a clinic spokeswoman who 
declined to give her name 
there are similar legal challenges to operation rescue 
demonstrations at abortion clinics in other states 
at todays hearing before us district judge louis f 
oberdorfer eisenstein showed videotapes of three november 
demonstrations in an effort to prove that operation rescue project 
rescue and their leaders violated oberdorfers injunction 
now and planned parenthood name five individuals as defendants 
along with the two organizations only one clifford gannett was 
in court today 
eisenstein said he would present witnesses to show that gannett 
was active in the blockades nov 11 and nov 17 at the hillcress 
womens surgicenter and the washington surgi clinic in violation 
of the order 
eisenstein also said he would show that organization rescue 
which says it is in debt spent well in excess of 50000 and 
maybe well more than 100000 on the november operations 
he said that 1989 donations to the two organizations exceeded 
700000 and that they deposited more than 11 million in bank 
accounts 
the high court monday rejected an emergency request by operation 
rescue members who said the atlanta injunctin is violating their 
freespeech rights 
