<TEXT>
miller brewing co said tuesday it will test a 
new barleyonly beer in four markets under a strategy to grab a 
bigger share of the shrinking market for superpremium beers 
the allmalt beer to be called miller reserve will be tested 
in rhode island connecticut richmond va and atlanta starting 
wednesday miller spokesman david fogelson said 
in brewing the product with only barley and no corn or other 
grain fillers the company is using the same approach as for some 
products made by smaller breweries that have grown rapidly in 
recent years 
miller reserve is brewed using a coldfiltered process in which 
contaminants are removed from the beer using a filtration system 
rather than heat pasteurization 
in miller reserve weve brought back the tradition of an 
allbarley beer and gone a step further by using our unique 
draftbrewing process said david krishock new products category 
director for the milwaukeebased brewery 
as light beers have continued growing in popularity the market 
share held by superpremium and import beers has slipped markedly in 
recent years miller hopes miller reserve will seize a portion of 
the shrinking market which averages about 16 million to 18 million 
barrels a year 
miller reserve is being brewed and shipped from the miller 
brewery at eden nc 
milwaukeebased frankenberry laughlin amp constable is to handle 
