<TEXT>
u s west inc said tuesday it will build new fiber 
optic phone lines for businesses in five cities that will heal 
themselves in the event of a failure 
the regional phone company also said it will offer a similar 
service to link various plants and buildings of a corporation or 
government agency 
the first service is aimed at improving the reliability of phone 
service to customers with medium to large amounts of data voice 
and video traffic by providing backup electronics and two separate 
fiberoptic lines through two telephone central offices 
several fiberoptic rings will be placed in each city with an 
average of 37 miles of fiber optics per city said hawk an average 
of 40 buildings in each city will be targeted for installation he 
said 
the service called alternate route protection will be offered 
in denver minneapolisst paul portland seattle and phoenix u s 
west said the service will be available starting in september in 
minneapolis with phoenix the last city on the companys 
installation schedule in july 1991 
with the convergence of data processing and 
telecommunications our customers networks carry traffic often 
representing millions of dollars they cant afford even one minute 
of downtime said bob hawk president of u s west communications 
carrier and information provider division 
with an availability rate of 9999 percent these new services 
virtually guarantee the highest reliability technically possible 
u s west said it will offer one month of free service if a 
customer suffers downtime while using the new services 
the second service the selfhealing network service is aimed 
at companies and government agencies with multiple locations 
u s west said two concentric fiberoptic rings will be installed 
linking the locations each employing devices that detect problems 
in the event of a failure the system would heal itself 
instantly by sending the transmission in the opposite direction 
around the ring u s west said 
